Kohi (coffee in japanese) is a library that provides some similar functions
to the library of Borland, conio.

How to use:

[1] create/install library.

   sudo make install

[2] build your binary.
 
   gcc -o my_app main.c -I/usr/local/include/ -L/usr/local/lib/ -lkohi

PS: main.c is the code of example application.


Uninstall library:

[1] run uninstall using Makefile.

   sudo make uninstall